prefix: Approach the following question the way someone with a PhD in engineering would.
problem_prompt:
Approach the following question the way someone with a PhD in engineering would. What is the molecular weight of 2-[(3S)-1-propylpyrrolidin-3-yl]acetonitrile?
Answer (numerical number):
gpt_response:
The molecular weight of 2-[(3S)-1-propylpyrrolidin-3-yl]acetonitrile can be calculated by first determining the molecular formula of the compound and then adding up the atomic weights of all the atoms present in the molecule. 

The molecular formula of 2-[(3S)-1-propylpyrrolidin-3-yl]acetonitrile is C11H19N2. 

Using the atomic weights of carbon (C = 12.01 g/mol), hydrogen (H = 1.008 g/mol), and nitrogen (N = 14.01 g/mol), we can calculate the molecular weight as follows:

(11 x 12.01) + (19 x 1.008) + (2 x 14.01) = 163.25 g/mol

Therefore, the molecular weight of 2-[(3S)-1-propylpyrrolidin-3-yl]acetonitrile is 163.25 g/mol.
